def is_cuttable_vegetable(vegetable:item):
    # Determine if an item is a cuttable vegetable
    symbol is_cuttable_vegetable = is_food_vegetable(vegetable) and cuttable(vegetable)
    return is_cuttable_vegetable

behavior clean_vegetable(vegetable:item, sink:item):
    body:
        achieve inside(vegetable, sink)
        # Place the vegetable inside the sink
        
        bind faucet: item where:
            is_faucet(faucet) and close(faucet, sink)
        # Identify a faucet close to the sink
        
        achieve_once is_on(faucet)
        # Turn the faucet on to clean the vegetable
        
        wash(vegetable)
        # Wash the vegetable
        
        achieve_once is_off(faucet)
        # Turn the faucet off

behavior cut_vegetable(vegetable:item, cutting_board:item, knife:item):
    body:
        achieve on(vegetable, cutting_board)
        # Place the vegetable on the cutting board

        achieve_once inhand(knife)
        # Temporarily hold the knife to cut the vegetable

        achieve cut(vegetable)
        # Achieve the cut state for the vegetable

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind sink: item where:
            is_sink(sink)
        # Select a sink

        bind cutting_board: item where:
            is_cutting_board(cutting_board)
        # Select a cutting board

        bind knife: item where:
            is_knife(knife)
        # Select a knife

        foreach vegetable: item:
            if is_cuttable_vegetable(vegetable):
                clean_vegetable(vegetable, sink)
                cut_vegetable(vegetable, cutting_board, knife)

def is_water_source(item: item):
    # Determine if the item is a source of water by evaluating if its a faucet near the stove
    symbol has_water_source = exists faucet: item : is_faucet(faucet) and close(faucet, item)
    return has_water_source

behavior fill_pot_with_water(pot: item, stove: item):
    body:
        if is_water_source(stove):
            achieve has_water(pot)
        else:
            foreach source: item:
                if is_faucet(source):
                    observe(source, "Is the faucet close enough to the stove for filling the pot wit
h water")

behavior start_to_boil(pot: item, stove: item):
    body:
        achieve plugged(stove)
        achieve is_on(stove)
        achieve on(pot, stove) # Place the pot on the stove
        achieve has_water(pot)

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind pot: item where:
            is_pot(pot) and close_char(char, pot)
        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove) and close_char(char, stove)
        
        fill_pot_with_water(pot, stove)
        start_to_boil(pot, stove)
